1
00:00:24,041 --> 00:00:25,708
Sister...? Sister!

2
00:00:25,791 --> 00:00:26,416
Komachi!

3
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,791
[KOMACHI] Sister!

4
00:00:28,875 --> 00:00:32,041
I'm sorry my
darling... it's okay.

5
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:35,500
The people of Kanna village

6
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:38,083
are like this firefly
gruel, Shichiroji.

7
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:39,875
A simpler food often ignored

8
00:00:39,958 --> 00:00:42,166
or thrown aside for
the heartier grain.

9
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:44,250
And we samurai are the cup...

10
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:46,875
A symbol of our duty to
protect those less fortunate

11
00:00:46,958 --> 00:00:49,416
than ourselves... Understand?

12
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,791
[SHICHIROJI] I understand
you're as kind as ever.

13
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:56,583
[KYUZO]
Do you want to die?

14
00:00:56,666 --> 00:01:00,125
I... I think you're...
you're an admirable person...

15
00:01:00,208 --> 00:01:04,083
That's all I wanted to say.
Forgive my rudeness.

16
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:12,416
[KATSUSHIRO]
Sensei, they're here! Sensei!

17
00:01:13,916 --> 00:01:15,708
It's time.

18
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:23,875
♪ opening song ♪

19
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:57,625
[THUNDER]

20
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,958
[KIRARA]
They've begun to move.

21
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:36,416
I can't see a thing, can you?

22
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:39,791
Great samurai,
I don't understand

23
00:03:39,875 --> 00:03:42,458
how you're able to see
the Bandits in all this rain?

24
00:03:42,541 --> 00:03:45,083
I don't have to
see them, Mosuke.

25
00:03:45,166 --> 00:03:46,375
They're machine samurai.

26
00:03:46,458 --> 00:03:48,416
I can hear them
from miles away.

27
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,500
Listen closely...

28
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:51,500
Be ready and do
exactly as I tell you.

29
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:53,541
It's the only way
to win this battle.

30
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:55,666
The Bandits are
counting on your fear.

31
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:56,916
If you succumb to it,

32
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,166
you'll be giving them
exactly what they want.

33
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:02,083
[THUNDER]

34
00:04:02,166 --> 00:04:03,125
[SHICHIROJI]
Coming up the waterfall

35
00:04:03,208 --> 00:04:04,916
is basic military strategy.

36
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,583
[KATSUSHIRO]
Even in this storm?

37
00:04:06,666 --> 00:04:09,333
The Nobuseri have learned
now what we samurai can do,

38
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,750
but they also know
the farmers are vulnerable.

39
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,958
They'll use any tactic
they can to intimidate,

40
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:16,458
and break their
fighting spirit.

41
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:20,208
A waterfall's a difficult
path for anybody to take...

42
00:04:20,291 --> 00:04:22,458
And this downpour will
make it even tougher.

43
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:23,708
But think of 
the advantages--

44
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:25,416
they can hide in the mist,
and their approach

45
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,375
won't be heard over
the roar of the water.

46
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:30,166
It's the kind of surprise attack
that sends farmers screaming.

47
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:32,125
But if it's such
a basic strategy,

48
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:34,958
won't they expect us to
have special defenses for it?

49
00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:36,958
That's very well
said, Katsushiro.

50
00:04:37,041 --> 00:04:40,208
You're beginning to reason
like a strategist, after all.

51
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:42,458
You must put yourself
in the enemy's camp.

52
00:04:42,541 --> 00:04:45,666
If you were attacking this
fortress, what would you do?

53
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:48,166
[RIKICHI]
The Bandits...! They're here!

54
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:49,833
On the western cliff
I saw a Raiden,

55
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:51,958
and eight Mimizuku
footsoldiers!

56
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,208
We've seen ten Mimizuku
on the southern path

57
00:04:54,291 --> 00:04:57,291
and twelve more up north,
plus three armored Yakan units!

58
00:04:57,375 --> 00:04:59,083
That many?!

59
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:00,500
[SHICHIROJI]
Those footsoldiers have proven

60
00:05:00,583 --> 00:05:02,541
to be tougher than we expected.

61
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:04,916
It looks like we're in
for one heck of a battle.

62
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,416
And the Benigumo?

63
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,916
[RIKICHI]
No sign of them yet.

64
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,541
Katsushiro, I want you and
Rikichi to make your way back to

65
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:13,333
Gorobei's post and assist him
in whatever way you can.

66
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:14,541
Right.

67
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:47,250
You've gotta be kidding.
Get down!

68
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:55,333
So, are you scared yet?

69
00:05:55,416 --> 00:05:56,625
Yep.

70
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,083
[MIMIZUKU 1]
Signal flare!

71
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:17,666
[YAKAN 1] We've breached
the southern wall.

72
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:23,875
You're gonna be okay.

73
00:06:23,958 --> 00:06:25,750
Get the wounded
out of here! Now!

74
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,125
Right...

75
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:29,375
[RIKICHI] Gosaku!

76
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:30,708
[GOSAKU]
Hurry, help me move them!

77
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:32,000
[RIKICHI] Yeah...

78
00:06:32,083 --> 00:06:32,958
[KATSUSHIRO]
What happened?

79
00:06:33,041 --> 00:06:34,208
They bombed us.

80
00:06:34,291 --> 00:06:36,166
The Bandits still have
bombs? That's forbidden!

81
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:38,750
At the end of the Great War...
such weapons were banned.

82
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:41,833
I need you to go back
and inform the others.

83
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:44,666
Of course, right away.

84
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:46,583
Rikichi, Gosaku,
tend to the wounded.

85
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:48,625
The rest of you follow me.

86
00:06:53,291 --> 00:06:56,291
The bandits are almost here--
We better get into position!

87
00:06:56,375 --> 00:06:57,666
[KIKUCHIYO]
Wait, wait, wait!

88
00:06:57,750 --> 00:07:00,250
You trigger-happy beasts!

89
00:07:01,916 --> 00:07:03,875
I attack first!

90
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:06,250
But Kambei told us
we had to attack togeth--

91
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:09,000
Eeoohh! Kambei told us!
I'm a samurai remember?!

92
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:10,791
I thought you told us you
were just a rice farmer,

93
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:13,458
like the rest of us.

94
00:07:13,541 --> 00:07:17,083
Shut your big trap or
I'll pound you into fertilizer!

95
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:18,000
[FARMERS YELL WORRIEDLY]

96
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:19,791
Th-Th-They-They're here!

97
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:35,208
What the hell...?

98
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:47,000
Come on, suckers!

99
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,375
[FARMERS GRUNT]

100
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:54,875
[KATSUSHIRO] I've checked
every post around the village.

101
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:57,416
There's a total
of six Mimizuku...

102
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,708
And they're
using bombs.

103
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:01,250
That means their Upper
Shrine has ordered

104
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,458
the use of forbidden weapons.

105
00:09:03,541 --> 00:09:05,625
The Bandits are
getting desperate.

106
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:08,708
They want to wipe Kanna
from the face of the planet.

107
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:27,625
They're here.

108
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:28,750
Good.

109
00:09:40,708 --> 00:09:41,458
[KATSUSHIRO GASPS]

110
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:42,625
[KATSUSHIRO YELLS]

111
00:09:50,458 --> 00:09:52,166
[KATSUSHIRO SCREAMS]

112
00:09:57,500 --> 00:10:00,833
[FARMERS YELL]

113
00:10:04,708 --> 00:10:07,333
Everything that my
family has is in there!

114
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:09,208
[REDHEAD FARMER]
Hurry! Put out the fire!

115
00:10:32,291 --> 00:10:33,875
[MANZO YELLS]

116
00:10:37,208 --> 00:10:38,916
I'm hit! I'm hit!
It's an arrow in my head!

117
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,583
I'm gonna die!
I don't want to die!

118
00:10:40,666 --> 00:10:43,958
It's not fair! Oh, my poor
Shino will be an orphan!

119
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:47,666
[KIKUCHIYO]
Quit bellyaching and run!

120
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:55,625
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

121
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:09,583
[KIKUCHIYO] Showoff.

122
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:34,791
[HEIHACHI GRUNTS]

123
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:46,708
[KATSUSHIRO
BREATHES HEAVILY]

124
00:13:46,791 --> 00:13:49,541
[SHICHIROJI] I tell ya,
those Mimizuku are a real pain.

125
00:13:49,625 --> 00:13:51,250
Yes... But get used to it

126
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:53,708
because there are
fifteen more left.

127
00:13:56,791 --> 00:13:58,916
Kikuchiyo, what are you
doing away from your post?

128
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,833
[KIKUCHIYO] Gotta get
one of these tooth picks.

129
00:14:00,916 --> 00:14:02,041
My sword broke.

130
00:14:02,125 --> 00:14:03,208
I mean, c'mon, there's
fighting everywhere!

131
00:14:03,291 --> 00:14:04,750
Who cares about posts?!

132
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:07,333
[EXPLOSION]

133
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:08,583
[FARMERS YELL]

134
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:15,750
[SHICHIROJI] Raiden?

135
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,083
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS ANGRILY]

136
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:20,208
[KAMBEI]
All of you stay back!

137
00:14:20,291 --> 00:14:23,583
[KIKUCHIYO]
Yeah, leave 'em to me! Ahhh!

138
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:26,666
[RIKICHI]
No, Kikuchiyo! Let me!

139
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:28,125
[KIKUCHIYO]
You Serious?

140
00:14:55,208 --> 00:14:56,958
[BLUE RAIDEN]
Foolish peasants.

141
00:14:57,041 --> 00:14:59,041
[RIKICHI GRUNTS]

142
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:01,750
Rikichi!

143
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:05,916
Are you all right?

144
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,333
[BLUE RAIDEN]
Heh. As if mere farmers

145
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:10,375
could wield a
Nobuseri weapon...!

146
00:15:10,458 --> 00:15:11,583
Kill them!

147
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:25,125
[BLUE RAIDEN]
Filthy traitor!

148
00:15:28,375 --> 00:15:29,416
[KATSUSHIRO YELLS]

149
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:47,083
Katsushiro...
don't be reckless.

150
00:15:47,166 --> 00:15:48,875
Yes, Sensei.

151
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:57,625
[KATSUSHIRO]
Are you hurt?

152
00:15:57,708 --> 00:15:59,000
[RIKICHI]
Don't worry about me.

153
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,333
[KATSUSHIRO] But...

154
00:16:00,416 --> 00:16:02,750
[MOSUKE] He has a broken rib,
but he'll be fine.

155
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,666
[RIKICHI] I thought we might do
some damage to the Bandits

156
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,875
if we could use their own
weapons against them...

157
00:16:06,958 --> 00:16:08,250
But what's the point
in even trying

158
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:11,083
if we get blown away doing it?

159
00:16:11,166 --> 00:16:13,833
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey, let go of me you bastards!

160
00:16:15,666 --> 00:16:16,958
Look Rikichi,

161
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,875
you want to live to see 
your wife again, don't you?

162
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:21,458
You should
be more careful.

163
00:16:21,541 --> 00:16:24,625
Take him to Lady Kirara's
house immediately.

164
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:39,583
That looks pretty serious.

165
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:47,250
Aw, nothing some
rice won't cure.

166
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,625
Gotta hate this rain, though--

167
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:50,708
makin' my moves
sloppier than normal.

168
00:16:50,791 --> 00:16:52,291
That'll happen.

169
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:54,291
[HEIHACHI]
Any bandits left?

170
00:16:54,375 --> 00:16:57,166
Only the Benigumo's patrol.

171
00:16:59,083 --> 00:17:00,375
Listen.

172
00:17:02,166 --> 00:17:04,791
[KIKUCHIYO] You are
seriously gonna regret this!

173
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:05,875
When you let go 
of me, I'm gonna--

174
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:07,916
Ah, Kikuchiyo!

175
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,791
[KIKUCHIYO] Wha-ah-ooh!

176
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,166
[GUNFIRE]

177
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:16,708
Kambei-sama,
is that the Benigumo?

178
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:19,083
We'll find out soon enough.

179
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:24,083
Good timing.

180
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:49,708
[KIKUCHIYO]
Time to finish you off.

181
00:17:52,291 --> 00:17:55,541
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

182
00:17:56,666 --> 00:17:58,166
What are you doing?

183
00:17:58,250 --> 00:18:00,958
[KIKUCHIYO] I had to replace 
my sword with something, right?

184
00:18:14,166 --> 00:18:15,458
[HEIHACHI GROANS]

185
00:18:28,625 --> 00:18:31,041
[KIKUCHIYO]
Now it's your turn.

186
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:32,541
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

187
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:36,916
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

188
00:18:43,458 --> 00:18:44,750
[GOROBEI] I see it!

189
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,583
Gorobei-dono!

190
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:54,833
[GOROBEI GRUNTS]

191
00:18:57,083 --> 00:18:58,541
You bastard!

192
00:18:58,625 --> 00:19:00,833
[KAMBEI] Wait.

193
00:19:00,916 --> 00:19:04,000
This is a battle
I must fight on my own.

194
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:12,500
[SYUSAI]
So we meet again, relic.

195
00:19:12,583 --> 00:19:14,125
[KAMBEI]
You're the only one left.

196
00:19:14,208 --> 00:19:15,916
[SYUSAI]
I figured as much.

197
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,791
[KAMBEI]
You've already lost.

198
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:22,708
What reason do you have to
continue attacking this village?

199
00:19:22,791 --> 00:19:25,791
Do you feel you have
something left to prove?

200
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,458
Is it because you're samurai?

201
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:32,916
[SYUSAI] The samurai
within me died ages ago!

202
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:45,083
[SYUSAI YELLS]

203
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:02,333
[SYUSAI YELLS]

204
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,083
[KIKUCHIYO]
That dirty little--!

205
00:20:14,958 --> 00:20:17,541
[SYUSAI SCREAMS]

206
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:21,416
[KAMBEI]
What are you doing?!

207
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:24,458
No one can kill
you except for me.

208
00:20:24,541 --> 00:20:26,916
He was never going to.

209
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,500
[SYUSAI YELLS]

210
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:39,208
Sensei!

211
00:20:39,291 --> 00:20:40,291
No, don't.

212
00:20:40,375 --> 00:20:41,833
But Gorobei-dono!

213
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:51,958
[EXPLOSION]

214
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:54,875
[SYUSAI SCREAMS]

215
00:21:04,375 --> 00:21:05,875
Rikichi.

216
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:07,791
Got him!
I can't believe we did it!

217
00:21:07,875 --> 00:21:09,750
[YOHEI]
Serves you right, bandit!

218
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:11,625
[SYUSAI] You...!

219
00:21:12,625 --> 00:21:15,625
You will regret that!

220
00:21:16,791 --> 00:21:18,708
[KAMBEI] Enough!

221
00:21:18,791 --> 00:21:20,833
[SYUSAI SCREAMS]

222
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:34,625
[LIGHT LAUGHTER]

223
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:40,583
[EXPLOSION]

224
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,333
[KIRARA]
The water's grown cloudy!

225
00:21:55,416 --> 00:21:57,000
What's that mean?

226
00:22:00,125 --> 00:22:02,541
Gorobei, you can't
die like this.

227
00:22:02,625 --> 00:22:05,166
You'll have to
forgive me, Rikichi...

228
00:22:05,250 --> 00:22:09,000
Looks like I can't take you
to the Capital, after all.

229
00:22:11,541 --> 00:22:13,916
Oh, Great Samurai.

230
00:22:15,541 --> 00:22:18,916
Your life... I've stolen it.

231
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:22,541
You... gotta be kidding... me.

232
00:22:25,666 --> 00:22:26,875
Gorobei-dono!

233
00:22:26,958 --> 00:22:27,916
[KIKUCHIYO] Gorobei!

234
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,125
Stop playing around,
you stupid mule!

235
00:22:30,208 --> 00:22:33,291
Come on, open your eyes.
This isn't funny!

236
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:37,708
We're responsible for this.

237
00:22:37,791 --> 00:22:39,208
Watch over things here.

238
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:40,958
You got it.

239
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:54,041
Great Kambei, wait!

240
00:22:54,125 --> 00:22:57,291
[ELDER]
Let him go.

241
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:59,000
He still has much to do.

242
00:22:59,083 --> 00:23:02,625
This battle may be won,
but the war is not.

243
00:23:13,375 --> 00:23:18,333
♪ closing song ♪

244
00:25:22,375 --> 00:25:23,500
[OKARA SNICKERS]

245
00:25:23,583 --> 00:25:25,375
[OKARA]
Hey there, it's me, Okara.

246
00:25:25,458 --> 00:25:27,958
You're not gonna believe what's
happening in Kanna lately!

247
00:25:28,041 --> 00:25:29,541
What is it, you ask?

248
00:25:29,625 --> 00:25:31,458
Well, if you'd stop asking me
dumb questions, I'd tell you!

249
00:25:31,541 --> 00:25:33,041
[OKARA SNICKERS]

250
00:25:33,125 --> 00:25:35,500
Our sleepy little village was
turned into a giant battlefield!

251
00:25:35,583 --> 00:25:37,291
The rain was pouring
down for hours

252
00:25:37,375 --> 00:25:39,666
and the ground was so
muddy you could hardly move,

253
00:25:39,750 --> 00:25:41,791
then all of a sudden we
were completely surrounded

254
00:25:41,875 --> 00:25:44,875
by big, ugly bandits as far
as the eye could see!

255
00:25:44,958 --> 00:25:46,291
But before they
knew what hit 'em,

256
00:25:46,375 --> 00:25:48,916
Kambei and the gang sliced
them up like rice stalks!

257
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:52,041
They didn't stand a chance
against our super-tough samurai!

258
00:25:52,125 --> 00:25:54,458
We gambled with
death, and won...

259
00:25:54,541 --> 00:25:57,250
Well, except for one of us...

260
00:25:57,333 --> 00:25:59,583
Gorobei's luck ran
out in the end.

261
00:25:59,666 --> 00:26:01,500
I guess that's part
of being a samurai.

262
00:26:01,583 --> 00:26:03,666
But he definitely wasn't
a weakling about it.

263
00:26:03,750 --> 00:26:05,833
He faced death
like a real warrior...

264
00:26:05,916 --> 00:26:09,333
And you can be sure my village
will never forget what he did...

265
00:26:09,416 --> 00:26:10,916
But enough of
this mushy stuff...

266
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,000
Hopefully after today,

267
00:26:12,083 --> 00:26:13,625
the Bandits won't
bother us anymore,

268
00:26:13,708 --> 00:26:16,458
because to be honest,
I'm sick of all the fighting...

269
00:26:16,541 --> 00:26:19,541
Well, I guess that's all
for now. See ya later!

